      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPER MOON (4) still a maiden but rarely out of the finish recording six placings from six starts. Was in the placings again last time finishing second (29.94) at The Gardens. Racing well and deserves a win. RHONDA'S RUPEES (7) made an eye-catching debut when charged out of the boxes with a slick early split and went straight to the front, giving a huge sight but headed late when a 2 length second (30.31) over 520m at this track. Shows good promise and should be in this for a long way. HER INDULGENCE (1) profiles well and boxed nicely for her debut. Worth keeping a close eye on the market. VOULEZ VROOM (2) will give backers a sight.",
